## **Appendix A ‚Äî Duckling Integration of the Coherence Ledger into the Mother Duck Temporal System**

To align temporal continuity with interpretative stability, we integrate the Coherence Ledger (CL-01) as a **Duckling** within the Mother Duck (MDL) subsystem. The duckling metaphor encodes hierarchical inheritance: MDL provides chronological structure, while CL-01 provides interpretative grounding.

Let ( MDL_t ) be the event ledger at time ( t ), and ( CL_t ) be the corresponding coherence entry. We define the coupling:

[
CL_t = f(MDL_t, I, A_t)
]

Where:

* ( I ) is the set of invariants
* ( A_t ) is the Hogge Attractor vector
* ( f() ) binds temporal order to meaning-space interpretation

Temporal ordering is inherited, but semantic structure is independently generated.

This integration prevents ‚Äúfloating interpretations‚Äù and ensures that all coherence decisions correspond to real events within the timeline, enabling stable reconstruction after resets and reducing entropy across the architecture.

